@page "/projects/projectlogo"
@using fishportfolio.Pages.Components

<PageTitle>Projects</PageTitle>
<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large">
    <MudPaper Class="px-8 py-4 my-3" Elevation="2">
        <Fishcrumbs />
        <MudText Class="ma-2" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.h1"><b>Logo project</b></MudText>
        <MudText Class="ma-2" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.body1">
            I needed a logo for myself to use on various projects of mine (including this site), so I designed one!
        </MudText>
        <MudDivider Style="background-color:#3aba9d; height:2px; opacity:0.7"></MudDivider>

        <MudGrid Class="my-2 pa-0" Spacing="0" Justify="Justify.Center">
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 pa-2" xs="12" sm="12">
                <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.h2"><b>Getting started</b></MudText>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="6">
                <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.body1">
                    First, I took a pencil and a sheet of paper and scribbled as many logo ideas as I could think of.
                    I let my mind go wild with designs, no matter how silly looking. This resulted in several designs I could compare and pick their best features to mold into one awesome logo 😃
                </MudText>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="6">
                <MudContainer Class="pa-0 ma-0">
                    <MudImage Class="pa-0 ma-0 rounded-lg" Fluid="true" ObjectFit="ObjectFit.Fill" Elevation="2" Src="./images/projectlogo/logo_draft_1.jpg" ObjectPosition="ObjectPosition.Center"></MudImage>
                    <MudText Class="d-flex justify-center ma-0 pa-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Center" Typo="Typo.caption">Lots of different ideas! 🤩</MudText>
                </MudContainer>
            </MudItem>

        </MudGrid>

        <MudDivider Style="background-color:#3aba9d; height:2px; opacity:0.7" />

        <MudGrid Class="my-2 pa-0" Spacing="0" Justify="Justify.Center">
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 pa-2" xs="12" sm="12">
                <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Right" Typo="Typo.h2"><b>Choosing the winner</b></MudText>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="4">
                <MudContainer Class="pa-0 ma-0">
                    <MudImage Class="pa-0 ma-0 rounded-lg" Fluid ObjectFit="ObjectFit.Fill" Elevation="2" Src="./images/projectlogo/logo_draft_2.jpg" ObjectPosition="ObjectPosition.Center"></MudImage>
                    <MudText Class="d-flex justify-center" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Center" Typo="Typo.caption">There could be only one 🏆</MudText>
                </MudContainer>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="8">
                <MudContainer Class="pa-0 ma-0">
                    <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Right" Typo="Typo.body1">
                        I really liked the swirly seal one, so I decided to improve on it. I was satisfied with the final draft.
                        At this point I felt I am ready to switch from pencil and paper and move on to digitalize my design.
                    </MudText>
                </MudContainer>
            </MudItem>
        </MudGrid>

        <MudDivider Style="background-color:#3aba9d; height:2px; opacity:0.7"></MudDivider>

        <MudGrid Class="my-2 pa-0" Spacing="0" Justify="Justify.Center">
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 pa-2" xs="12" sm="12">
                <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.h2"><b>Going digital</b></MudText>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="12">
                <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.body1">
                    After uploading a photo of the sketch, I began tracing it using InkScape software.
                    Another step in designing the logo was to choose the right color palette. Once again I brainstormed some ideas and put them side by side.
                    I even asked my friends for advice as to which one they personally found fitting.
                </MudText>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="my-2 px-2" xs="12" sm="12">
                <MudContainer Class="pa-0 ma-0">
                    <MudImage Class="pa-0 ma-0 rounded-lg" Fluid ObjectFit="ObjectFit.Fill" Elevation="2" Src="./images/projectlogo/logo_draft_3.png" ObjectPosition="ObjectPosition.Center"></MudImage>
                    <MudText Class="d-flex justify-center" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Center" Typo="Typo.caption">Tough decision 😅</MudText>
                </MudContainer>
            </MudItem>

        </MudGrid>

        <MudDivider Style="background-color:#3aba9d; height:2px; opacity:0.7"></MudDivider>

        <MudGrid Class="my-2 pa-0" Spacing="0" Justify="Justify.Center">
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 pa-2" xs="12" sm="12">
                <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.h2"><b>Final designs</b></MudText>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="4">
                <MudContainer Class="pa-0 ma-0">
                    <MudText Class="pa-0 ma-0" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Left" Typo="Typo.body1">
                        After some more polishing, my final designs were ready. The logo comes in two verisons: color and transparent.
                    </MudText>
                </MudContainer>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem Class="ma-0 px-2" xs="12" sm="8">
                <MudContainer Class="pa-0 ma-0">
                    <MudImage Class="pa-0 ma-0 rounded-lg" Fluid ObjectFit="ObjectFit.Fill" Elevation="2" Src="./images/projectlogo/logos_final.png" ObjectPosition="ObjectPosition.Center" Style="background-color:#061713"></MudImage>
                    <MudText Class="d-flex justify-center" Color="Color.Primary" Align="Align.Center" Typo="Typo.caption">Final designs 🥳</MudText>
                </MudContainer>
            </MudItem>
        </MudGrid>


    </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>